text: Hinds County is a county located in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2020 census, the population was 227,742. It is the most populous county in Mississippi. Its county seats are Raymond and Jackson, the state capital. The county was created in 1821. It is named for General Thomas Hinds, a hero of the Battle of New Orleans during the War of 1812. == References == == Other websites == * Hinds County - Official website Category:1820s establishments in Mississippi Category:1821 establishments in Mississippi
